<HEADLINE>
<P>
MANDATORY STATE QUAKE INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So, Gov. George Deukmejian and the gang have decided that earthquake insurance 
is such a good idea that they have the right to force every homeowner to buy 
some whether he wants it or not. 
</P>
<P>
I have a few questions, though. 
</P>
<P>
Where does the government get the power to force people to insure their private 
property? Why does the government think it is proper to engage in a business 
that is best handled by private enterprise? Why is it proper for the government 
to seize a person's property because he refuses to insure it? When did we, the 
people, decide that government should do our thinking for us? 
</P>
<P>
Thanks, Gov. Deukmejian. You have convinced me to vote Libertarian. 
</P>
<P>
BROCK BACKLUND 
</P>
<P>
Calabasas 
</P>
</TEXT>
