<HEADLINE>
<P>
KINGS ASSIGN ALLISON TO PHOENIX AFFILIATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HULL, Quebec 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ten-year NHL veteran Mike Allison was assigned to the International Hockey 
League Phoenix Roadrunners by the Kings on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
"Mike is not in our plans right now, and this gives us a chance to take a long 
look at some of the kids," King General Manager Rogie Vachon said. 
</P>
<P>
Allison, 29, played for the New York Rangers and Toronto Maple Leafs before 
coming to the Kings in December, 1987. He had two goals and 11 assists last 
season. His NHL totals are 102 goals and 166 assists for 268 points. 
</P>
<P>
Allison will report to Phooenix next Thursday. 
</P>
