<TEXT>
<P>
In other water polo matches: 
</P>
<P>
Crespi 7, Santa Monica 5 -- Crespi remained undefeated in seven matches with a 
nonleague victory at Santa Monica (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Crespi driver Rusty King had three goals and Vince Greco added two. Crespi 
goalie Tim Behrens recorded 12 saves. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 17, Crespi 43 -- Senior Eddie Diaz timed 17 minutes 23 seconds on 
the three-mile course at Pierce College as the Knights swept the top four 
places and ended a five-year drought against the Celts in the Mission League 
opener for both schools. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade d. Louisville, 15-7, 15-5, 15-8 -- Pam Powers recorded 12 kills and 
Noelle Nonaka 20 assists as the Eagles (2-1) notched their first win over the 
Royals (0-2) in five years in a nonleague match at Chaminade. 
</P>
<P>
Royal d. Arcadia, 15-3, 15-9, 15-4 -- Stacy Kaufmann and Becky Campbell each 
had seven kills and Kaufmann added seven digs as the Highlanders improved to 
2-0 with a nonleague win at home. 
</P>
<P>
Montclair Prep d. Buckley, 15-9, 15-10, 15-4 -- Maria Cicione (nine kills) and 
Kendra Dousette (seven) led Montclair Prep (2-0) in a nonleague game at 
Buckley. 
</P>
<P>
La Reina d. Santa Paula, 15-12, 15-1, 15-7 -- Amy Crotty, a setter, had nine 
kills to pace host La Reina (2-0) and Shannon Mahan added five kills for the 
winners in a nonleague match. 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs d. Bell-Jeff, 15-13, 15-17, 15-2, 15-11 -- Jennifer Wagner had 29 
kills and 14 blocks for Burroughs (3-0) in a nonleague match at Burroughs. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. Baptist d. Oak Park, 15-7, 5-15, 15-2, 11-15, 15-10 -- Outside hitter 
Monica Davis had 10 kills and Amy Anderson added 19 assists for L.A. Baptist 
(2-0) in a nonleague match at Oak Park. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks d. Notre Dame, 15-12, 10-15, 15-3, 15-5 -- Aimee Stone had 10 
kills for Thousand Oaks in a nonleague match at Notre Dame (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
Setter Jennifer Streltzoff had 36 assists for Thousand Oaks (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
North Texas 1, The Master's College 0 -- Tommy St. John scored the only goal of 
the match at the 19-minute mark of the first half in a nonconference match in 
Denton, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
North Texas, a Division I school, outshot Master's, 18-9. Goalkeeper Allan 
Bowden recorded five saves for Master's (2-2-1). 
</P>
