<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HARVARD STAGES A WATER POLO CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ADAM BENSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Siman had been out of water polo for six seasons before he returned to 
coach at Buena High this season. 
</P>
<P>
Thursday night, he saw what he had been missing. 
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately the demonstration came from Buena's opponent, Harvard High, which 
defeated Buena, 20-2, in the first round of the Millikan tournament at Wilson 
High in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
"They were intense, fast and aggressive," Siman said. "I hope to see my team 
play the same way." 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore Jim Toring scored five goals, three in the third period, and Mark 
Townsend and Ryan Salceda each scored three goals for Harvard (2-0). Brian 
Border and Matt DeFronzo each scored twice. 
</P>
<P>
"We are starting to come together as a team," Harvard Coach Rich Corso said. 
"The chemistry is already there and the kids are feeling good." 
</P>
<P>
Harvard will play Anaheim Canyon in the second round today at 1:30 p.m. at 
Wilson High. ADAM BENSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
