<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: VENTURA FREEWAY WORK TO CLOSE LANES, RAMPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some lanes and ramps on the Ventura Freeway in the San Fernando Valley will be 
closed tonight and Saturday night because of work to widen the freeway, 
Caltrans announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
From 11 p.m. today to 9 a.m. Saturday, up to three eastbound lanes will be 
closed between Hazeltine Avenue and the Tujunga Wash bridge. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the eastbound Woodman Avenue and Coldwater Canyon Avenue on- and 
off-ramps will be closed during the same hours. 
</P>
<P>
From 11 p.m. Saturday to 9 a.m. Sunday, up to three eastbound lanes will be 
closed between Fulton and Colfax avenues, California Department of 
Transportation officials said. 
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the eastbound Coldwater Canyon Avenue and Laurel Canyon 
Boulevard on- and off-ramps also will be closed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
