<HEADLINE>
<P>
GULF CRISIS REVIVES OLD PALESTINE ORANIZATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DHAHRAN, Saudi Arabia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A moribund Palestinian organization replaced by the Palestine Liberation 
Organization more than 25 years ago has resurfaced because of Arab anger with 
the PLO's stand in the Persian Gulf crisis. 
</P>
<P>
The Supreme Arab Committee for Palestine released its first statement in a year 
this week to criticize "Palestinians who are supporting Iraq against Saudi 
Arabia." The committee's statement, released in New York, was published in the 
widely read Saudi-owned newspaper Asharq al Awsat. 
</P>
