Fax machines have been airlifted to U.S. troops in the Persian Gulf so they may 
receive up-to-the-minute news from home in addition to letters and packages, a 
spokesman for Sen. Alan Cranston (D-Calif.) said Thursday. Communications 
companies including ATT, MCI and Sprint are participating in the fax airlift, 
the spokesman said. 
</P>
