</P>
<P>
JEFFREY-LYNNE SITE OF HEALTH FAIR SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Homemade Latino foods, children's games, dance groups and live music will be 
some of the features at the first Health Fair in the streets of the 
Jeffrey-Lynne neighborhood behind Disneyland on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Lynne Avenue, the main street through the small, low-income community, will be 
filled Saturday morning with health agencies offering free services including 
measles vaccinations, blood pressure readings and AIDS tests. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, several social service agencies will staff booths with 
representatives to answer questions about housing, immigration services, 
employment and legal aid. 
</P>
<P>
"The incentive is, if they go to the health screenings, they'll get a free 
ticket for the booth games," said Anita Castro-Zvoda, director of the 
Jeffrey-Lynne Community Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
