<P>
UCLA Forecasters Expect Recession: The nation's economy is moving toward a 
full-blown recession that will last for the next six months, according to the 
UCLA Business Forecasting Project. 
</P>
<P>
The forecasters said they expected real gross national product to decline for 
two quarters, beginning in the fourth quarter, with drops of 2.4% and 3.2%, 
respectively, before recovering again. Such a decline would be the first since 
1982. The forecast predicted an overall GNP growth of 0.9% for this year. 
</P>
