<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mike Flagg Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction Statistics: The slowdown in office construction in Orange County 
has also been noticed by the Construction Industry Research Board, which 
gathers building statistics for the industry. 
</P>
<P>
In fact, says the board, construction of office buildings is down almost 
everywhere in the state. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange County, permits for office construction dropped by a third in value 
during the first seven months of the year, from $210 million to $140 million. 
</P>
<P>
Store construction was up in the county, as it was across the state. But 
construction of industrial buildings fell in the county, the board said, by 
about 22%. Last year, local governments issued permits for $70 million worth of 
industrial construction, compared to $54 million in the first seven months of 
1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
