<P>
POLES HAIL 'FATHER' REAGAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WARSAW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Poland today welcomed former President Ronald Reagan as the true father of 
Eastern Europe's democratic revolution, and he returned the compliment, saying 
it was the Poles who showed the world how to break the grip of communism. 
</P>
<P>
"Here . . . you began the global democratic revolution that is sweeping every 
continent and touching every people," Reagan said to warm applause on the first 
day of a two-day visit to Poland. 
</P>
<P>
"You and your countrymen have won more than the admiration of the world for 
launching your democratic revolution," he told senators, deputies and ministers 
at a ceremony at Warsaw's Royal Castle. "You have won the world's respect for 
restoring your nation's independence against all odds." 
</P>
